# Epic 8: Building the Flask Web Application

## Overview

Epic 8 focuses on developing and deploying a Flask-based web application for the **Human Development Index (HDI) Prediction System**. The application integrates the trained Linear Regression model with an interactive web interface, enabling users to input socio-economic indicators and receive predicted HDI scores in real time.

The Flask framework handles routing, user requests, model loading, prediction processing, and rendering HTML pages, providing a complete end-to-end deployment of the machine learning model.

---

## Objective

- Develop the Flask backend.
- Load the trained machine learning model.
- Create interactive web pages.
- Process user inputs.
- Generate HDI predictions.
- Deploy and test the complete application.

---

## Tasks Completed

### Task 1: Writing the Flask Backend

- Imported Flask, Pickle, and NumPy libraries.
- Initialized the Flask application.
- Loaded the saved `hdi_model.pkl`.
- Created the home (`/`) route.
- Created the prediction (`/predict`) route.
- Processed user inputs and generated HDI predictions.

### Task 2: Running the Application

- Executed the Flask application locally.
- Verified navigation between the Home and Prediction pages.
- Accepted user inputs through HTML forms.
- Generated HDI predictions using the trained Linear Regression model.
- Displayed prediction results successfully on the web interface.

---

